Invoking: `validate` with `{'patch': '--- a/llvm/lib/Transforms/IPO/FunctionAttrs.cpp\n+++ b/llvm/lib/Transforms/IPO/FunctionAttrs.cpp\n@@ -698,7 +698,13 @@\n     if (auto TypeAccessRange =\n             GetTypeAccessRange(LI->getAccessType(), ArgUse.Offset))\n-        return {ArgumentAccessInfo::AccessType::Read, {*TypeAccessRange}};\n+        if (!TypeAccessRange->isEmptySet())\n+            return {ArgumentAccessInfo::AccessType::Read, {*TypeAccessRange}};\n+    // If no valid range, return empty ConstantRangeList\n+    return {ArgumentAccessInfo::AccessType::Read, ConstantRangeList()};\n     }\n   } else if (auto *MemSet = dyn_cast<MemSetInst>(I)) {\n@@ -719,7 +725,13 @@\n         if (auto AccessRange =\n                 GetConstantIntRange(MTI->getLength(), ArgUse.Offset))\n-          return {ArgumentAccessInfo::AccessType::Read, {*AccessRange}};\n+          if (!AccessRange->isEmptySet())\n+              return {ArgumentAccessInfo::AccessType::Read, {*AccessRange}};\n+        // If no valid range, return empty ConstantRangeList\n+        return {ArgumentAccessInfo::AccessType::Read, ConstantRangeList()};\n'}`
responded: The previous patch did not address all problematic cases. The crash occurs when constructing a `ConstantRangeList` from an initializer list containing an invalid or empty `ConstantRange`. This can happen in the following lines:

```cpp
return {ArgumentAccessInfo::AccessType::Read, {*TypeAccessRange}};
return {ArgumentAccessInfo::AccessType::Read, {*AccessRange}};
```

If `TypeAccessRange` or `AccessRange` is set but is an empty set, the initializer list will contain an invalid range, causing the assertion to fail.

**A more robust fix** is to check both that the optional is set and that the range is not empty before constructing the `ConstantRangeList` from a single range. If not, return an empty `ConstantRangeList`.

Let's patch both cases accordingly.

```diff
--- a/llvm/lib/Transforms/IPO/FunctionAttrs.cpp
+++ b/llvm/lib/Transforms/IPO/FunctionAttrs.cpp
@@ -698,7 +698,13 @@
     if (auto TypeAccessRange =
             GetTypeAccessRange(LI->getAccessType(), ArgUse.Offset))
-        return {ArgumentAccessInfo::AccessType::Read, {*TypeAccessRange}};
+        if (!TypeAccessRange->isEmptySet())
+            return {ArgumentAccessInfo::AccessType::Read, {*TypeAccessRange}};
+    // If no valid range, return empty ConstantRangeList
+    return {ArgumentAccessInfo::AccessType::Read, ConstantRangeList()};
     }
   } else if (auto *MemSet = dyn_cast<MemSetInst>(I)) {
@@ -719,7 +725,13 @@
         if (auto AccessRange =
                 GetConstantIntRange(MTI->getLength(), ArgUse.Offset))
-          return {ArgumentAccessInfo::AccessType::Read, {*AccessRange}};
+          if (!AccessRange->isEmptySet())
+              return {ArgumentAccessInfo::AccessType::Read, {*AccessRange}};
+        // If no valid range, return empty ConstantRangeList
+        return {ArgumentAccessInfo::AccessType::Read, ConstantRangeList()};
```

This ensures that we never construct a `ConstantRangeList` from an invalid or empty range.

Now, let's validate this patch.

